  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.10.1\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nsnapshot prune-state can survive running out of disk space without corrupting the DB\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nA user with < 25 GiB free before starting snapshot prune-state reports that the process \"hung\" at DB compaction, and he was left with a corrupted DB.\r\n\r\nAdditional feedback from user: \"best i can remember was that it was only 3 lines of compacting, then i went to sleep and woke up and 10 hours later it was on the third status like still. meaning, it looked like it wasn’t progressing after 10 hours.\"\r\n",
